Two Weeks Later [id=fba3_followup_section]
----------------

::fba3_progress_graph_2 [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="Follow-Up Progress"]

JJ: Wait — that's way better! [face=awe]

Annie: Right?! My roommate is so much happier. Johnny is going to bed on time most nights now. His parents even asked her what her secret was! [face=smileBig]

JJ: So we didn't even need a whole new plan after all. [face=smile]

Lin: That's exactly the point. Look at what actually changed between Round 1 and Round 2. The intervention strategy was almost the same. We didn't redesign the plan — we made it easier to follow. The fidelity changed, and the results followed. [face=serious]

JJ: Okay, I hear you. I was ready to start from scratch, and it turned out the plan was fine — we just needed to support the person doing it. That's... actually a really important lesson. [face=explaining]

